race.comment: TRACK PATCHER (3) has raced twice this prep and hasn't bothered the judge on either occasion. Steps up to a more suitable trip and drops in class this time. Had a jump-out since the last run so he should be ready to show something like his best. QUBELLA (12) opened this prep with a couple of wins at the picnics then stormed home late and just missed the hat trick at Kerang recently. Unproven at the mile but that latest effort suggests she is ready for another crack. TIGHT GRIP (2) ran a better race last start when in the money at Cranbourne over today's journey. Down in class and can feature again. KYOKUSHIN (15) was better last time at Yarra Valley and can measure up here.
